--- title: "Adobe Analytics APIs v1 - Build: 2019-10-03_20:32:29.323" language_tabs: - shell: Shell - http: HTTP - javascript: JavaScript - ruby: Ruby - python: Python - php: PHP - java: Java - go: Go toc_footers: [] includes: [] search: true highlight_theme: darkula headingLevel: 2 ---

Adobe Analytics APIs v1 - Build: 2019-10-03_20:32:29.323

> Scroll down for code samples, example requests and responses. Select a language for code samples from the tabs above or the mobile navigation menu. The endpoints described here are routed through Adobe.io. In order to use these endpoints you must create an oAuth client that is subscribed to access the Adobe Analytics Reporting API. Base URLs: * https://analytics.adobe.io/

calculatedmetrics

## findCalculatedMetrics > Code samples ```shell curl --request GET \ --url 'https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE' \ --header 'content-type: application/json' ``` ```node const request = require('request'); const options = { method: 'GET', url: 'https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics', qs: { rsids: 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', ownerId: 'SOME_INTEGER_VALUE', filterByIds: 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', toBeUsedInRsid: 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', locale: 'en_US', name: 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', tagNames: 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', favorite: 'SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE', approved: 'SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE', limit: '10', page: '0', sortDirection: 'ASC', sortProperty: 'id', expansion: 'SOME_ARRAY_VALUE', includeType: 'SOME_ARRAY_VALUE' }, headers: {'content-type': 'application/json'} }; request(options, function (error, response, body) { if (error) throw new Error(error); console.log(body); }); ``` ```php setUrl('https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics'); $request->setMethod(HTTP_METH_GET); $request->setQueryData([ 'rsids' => 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', 'ownerId' => 'SOME_INTEGER_VALUE', 'filterByIds' => 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', 'toBeUsedInRsid' => 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', 'locale' => 'en_US', 'name' => 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', 'tagNames' => 'SOME_STRING_VALUE', 'favorite' => 'SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE', 'approved' => 'SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE', 'limit' => '10', 'page' => '0', 'sortDirection' => 'ASC', 'sortProperty' => 'id', 'expansion' => 'SOME_ARRAY_VALUE', 'includeType' => 'SOME_ARRAY_VALUE' ]); $request->setHeaders([ 'content-type' => 'application/json' ]); try { $response = $request->send(); echo $response->getBody(); } catch (HttpException $ex) { echo $ex; } ``` ```java HttpResponse response = Unirest.get("https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE") .header("content-type", "application/json") .asString(); ``` ```go package main import ( "fmt" "net/http" "io/ioutil" ) func main() { url := "https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE" req, _ := http.NewRequest("GET", url, nil) req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json") res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req) defer res.Body.Close() body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body) fmt.Println(res) fmt.Println(string(body)) } ``` ```python import http.client conn = http.client.HTTPSConnection("analytics.adobe.io") headers = { 'content-type': "application/json" } conn.request("GET", "/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE", headers=headers) res = conn.getresponse() data = res.read() print(data.decode("utf-8")) ``` ```csharp var client = new RestClient("https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE"); var request = new RestRequest(Method.GET); request.AddHeader("content-type", "application/json"); IRestResponse response = client.Execute(request); ``` ```ruby require 'uri' require 'net/http' require 'openssl' url = URI("https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?rsids=SOME_STRING_VALUE&ownerId=SOME_INTEGER_VALUE&filterByIds=SOME_STRING_VALUE&toBeUsedInRsid=SOME_STRING_VALUE&locale=en_US&name=SOME_STRING_VALUE&tagNames=SOME_STRING_VALUE&favorite=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&approved=SOME_BOOLEAN_VALUE&limit=10&page=0&sortDirection=ASC&sortProperty=id&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE&includeType=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE") http = Net::HTTP.new(url.host, url.port) http.use_ssl = true http.verify_mode = OpenSSL::SSL::VERIFY_NONE request = Net::HTTP::Get.new(url) request["content-type"] = 'application/json' response = http.request(request) puts response.read_body ``` `GET /calculatedmetrics` *Retrieve many calculated metrics* A calculated metric response will always include these default items: *id, name, description, rsid, owner, polarity, precision, type* Other attributes can be optionally requested through the 'expansion' field: * *modified*: Date that the metric was last modified (ISO 8601) * *definition*: Calculated metric definition as JSON object * *compatibility*: Products that the metric is compatible with * *reportSuiteName*: Also return the friendly Report Suite name for the RSID * *tags*: Gives all existing tags associated with the calculated metric For more information about calculated metrics go [here](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/analytics-2.0-apis/blob/master/calculatedmetrics.md)

Parameters

|Name|In|Type|Required|Description| |---|---|---|---|---| |rsids|query|string|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics tied to specified RSID list (comma-delimited)| |ownerId|query|integer(int32)|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics owned by the specified loginId| |filterByIds|query|string|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics in the specified list (comma-delimited list of IDs) (this is the same as calculatedMetricFilter, and is overwritten by calculatedMetricFilter| |toBeUsedInRsid|query|string|false|The report suite where the calculated metric intended to be used. This report suite will be used to determine things like compatibility and permissions. If it is not specified then the permissions will be calculated based on the union of all metrics authorized in all groups the user belongs to. If the compatibility expansion is specified and toBeUsedInRsid is not then the compatibility returned is based off the compatibility from the last time the calculated metric was saved.| |locale|query|string|false|Locale| |name|query|string|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics that contains the Name| |tagNames|query|string|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics that contains one of the tags| |favorite|query|boolean|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics that are favorites| |approved|query|boolean|false|Filter list to only include calculated metrics that are approved| |limit|query|integer|false|Number of results per page| |page|query|integer|false|Page number (base 0 - first page is "0")| |sortDirection|query|string|false|Sort direction (ASC or DESC)| |sortProperty|query|string|false|Property to sort by (name, modified_date, id is currently allowed)| |expansion|query|array[string]|false|Comma-delimited list of additional calculated metric metadata fields to include on response.| |includeType|query|array[string]|false|Include additional calculated metrics not owned by user. The "all" option takes precedence over "shared"| #### Enumerated Values |Parameter|Value| |---|---| |expansion|reportSuiteName| |expansion|ownerFullName| |expansion|modified| |expansion|tags| |expansion|definition| |expansion|compatibility| |expansion|categories| |expansion|reportSuiteName| |expansion|ownerFullName| |expansion|modified| |expansion|tags| |expansion|definition| |expansion|compatibility| |expansion|categories| |includeType|all| |includeType|shared| |includeType|templates| |includeType|all| |includeType|shared| |includeType|templates| > Example responses > 200 Response ```json { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "required": [ "definition" ], "properties": { "id": { "type": "string", "description": "System generated id", "readOnly": true }, "name": { "type": "string" }, "description": { "type": "string" }, "rsid": { "type": "string", "description": "The report suite id for which the component was created/updated" }, "reportSuiteName": { "type": "string", "description": "The report suite name for which the component was created/updated", "readOnly": true }, "owner": { "type": "object", "required": [ "id" ], "properties": { "id": { "type": "integer", "format": "int32", "description": "the login id of the owner" }, "name": { "type": "string", "position": 1, "description": "the friendly full login name of the owner, included when the expansion parameter ownerFullName is true" }, "login": { "type": "string", "position": 1, "description": "the friendly full login name of the owner, included when the expansion parameter ownerFullName is true" } } }, "polarity": { "type": "string", "description": "Set metric polarity, which indicates whether it's good or bad if a given metric goes up. Default=positive", "enum": [ "positive", "negative" ] }, "precision": { "type": "integer", "format": "int32", "description": "Number of decimal places to include in calculated metric result" }, "type": { "type": "string", "enum": [ "CURRENCY", "TIME", "DECIMAL", "PERCENT" ] }, "definition": { "type": "object" }, "categories": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }, "tags": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "id": { "type": "integer", "format": "int32", "description": "the tag id" }, "name": { "type": "string", "description": "the tag name " }, "description": { "type": "string", "description": "the tag description" }, "components": { "type": "array", "description": "the list of components that have been tagged with this tag", "uniqueItems": true, "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "componentType": { "type": "string" }, "componentId": { "type": "string" }, "tags": { "type": "array", "items": "[Circular]" } } } } }, "description": "Tag Model" } }, "siteTitle": { "type": "string" }, "modified": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }, "created": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time", "description": "Calculated metric creation date", "readOnly": true } } } } ```

Responses

|Status|Meaning|Description|Schema| |---|---|---|---| |200|[OK](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.3.1)|successful operation|Inline| |400|[Bad Request](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.1)|Unable to retrieve list of calculated metrics shared with user|[CalculatedMetricErrorStatus](#schemacalculatedmetricerrorstatus)| |401|[Unauthorized](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section-3.1)|Owner filter error; user specified is not in the same company as the requesting user|[CalculatedMetricErrorStatus](#schemacalculatedmetricerrorstatus)| |403|[Forbidden](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.3)|Requesting non-shared calculated metrics for other users is restricted to admin users|[CalculatedMetricErrorStatus](#schemacalculatedmetricerrorstatus)| |500|[Internal Server Error](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.6.1)|External API error; Calculated metric retrieval failed|[CalculatedMetricErrorStatus](#schemacalculatedmetricerrorstatus)|

Response Schema

Status Code **200** |Name|Type|Required|Restrictions|Description| |---|---|---|---|---| |*anonymous*|[[AnalyticsCalculatedMetric](#schemaanalyticscalculatedmetric)]|false|none|none| |» id|string|false|read-only|System generated id| |» name|string|false|none|none| |» description|string|false|none|none| |» rsid|string|false|none|The report suite id for which the component was created/updated| |» reportSuiteName|string|false|read-only|The report suite name for which the component was created/updated| |» owner|[Owner](#schemaowner)|false|none|none| |»» id|integer(int32)|true|none|the login id of the owner| |»» name|string|false|none|the friendly full login name of the owner, included when the expansion parameter ownerFullName is true| |»» login|string|false|none|the friendly full login name of the owner, included when the expansion parameter ownerFullName is true| |» polarity|string|false|none|Set metric polarity, which indicates whether it's good or bad if a given metric goes up. Default=positive| |» precision|integer(int32)|false|none|Number of decimal places to include in calculated metric result| |» type|string|false|none|none| |» definition|[CalculatedMetricDef](#schemacalculatedmetricdef)|true|none|none| |» categories|[string]|false|none|none| |» tags|[[Tag](#schematag)]|false|none|[Tag Model]| |»» id|integer(int32)|false|none|the tag id| |»» name|string|false|none|the tag name| |»» description|string|false|none|the tag description| |»» components|[[TaggedComponent](#schemataggedcomponent)]|false|none|the list of components that have been tagged with this tag| |»»» componentType|string|false|none|none| |»»» componentId|string|false|none|none| |»»» tags|[[Tag](#schematag)]|false|none|Tag Model| |» siteTitle|string|false|none|none| |» modified|string(date-time)|false|none|none| |» created|string(date-time)|false|read-only|Calculated metric creation date| #### Enumerated Values |Property|Value| |---|---| |polarity|positive| |polarity|negative| |type|CURRENCY| |type|TIME| |type|DECIMAL| |type|PERCENT|
This operation does not require authentication

``` ```go package main import ( "fmt" "strings" "net/http" "io/ioutil" ) func main() { url := "https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?locale=en_US&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE" payload := strings.NewReader("{\"name\":\"string\",\"description\":\"string\",\"rsid\":\"string\",\"owner\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"login\":\"string\"},\"polarity\":\"positive\",\"precision\":0,\"type\":\"CURRENCY\",\"definition\":{},\"categories\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"description\":\"string\",\"components\":[{\"componentType\":\"string\",\"componentId\":\"string\",\"tags\":[{}]}]}],\"siteTitle\":\"string\",\"modified\":\"2019-08-24T14:15:22Z\"}") req, _ := http.NewRequest("POST", url, payload) req.Header.Add("accept", "application/json") req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json") res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req) defer res.Body.Close() body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body) fmt.Println(res) fmt.Println(string(body)) } ``` ```python import http.client conn = http.client.HTTPSConnection("analytics.adobe.io") payload = "{\"name\":\"string\",\"description\":\"string\",\"rsid\":\"string\",\"owner\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"login\":\"string\"},\"polarity\":\"positive\",\"precision\":0,\"type\":\"CURRENCY\",\"definition\":{},\"categories\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"description\":\"string\",\"components\":[{\"componentType\":\"string\",\"componentId\":\"string\",\"tags\":[{}]}]}],\"siteTitle\":\"string\",\"modified\":\"2019-08-24T14:15:22Z\"}" headers = { 'accept': "application/json", 'content-type': "application/json" } conn.request("POST", "/calculatedmetrics?locale=en_US&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE", payload, headers) res = conn.getresponse() data = res.read() print(data.decode("utf-8")) ``` ```csharp var client = new RestClient("https://analytics.adobe.io/calculatedmetrics?locale=en_US&expansion=SOME_ARRAY_VALUE"); --- title: Swagger Petstore v1.0.0 language_tabs: - shell: Shell - http: HTTP - javascript: JavaScript - ruby: Ruby - python: Python - php: PHP - java: Java - go: Go toc_footers: - Find out how to create Github repo for your OpenAPI spec. includes: [] search: true highlight_theme: darkula headingLevel: 2 ---

Swagger Petstore v1.0.0

> Scroll down for code samples, example requests and responses. Select a language for code samples from the tabs above or the mobile navigation menu. This is a sample server Petstore server. You can find out more about Swagger at [http://swagger.io](http://swagger.io) or on [irc.freenode.net, #swagger](http://swagger.io/irc/). For this sample, you can use the api key `special-key` to test the authorization filters. # Introduction This API is documented in **OpenAPI format** and is based on [Petstore sample](http://petstore.swagger.io/) provided by [swagger.io](http://swagger.io) team. It was **extended** to illustrate features of [generator-openapi-repo](https://github.com/Rebilly/generator-openapi-repo) tool and [ReDoc](https://github.com/Redocly/redoc) documentation. In addition to standard OpenAPI syntax we use a few [vendor extensions](https://github.com/Redocly/redoc/blob/master/docs/redoc-vendor-extensions.md). # OpenAPI Specification This API is documented in **OpenAPI format** and is based on [Petstore sample](http://petstore.swagger.io/) provided by [swagger.io](http://swagger.io) team. It was **extended** to illustrate features of [generator-openapi-repo](https://github.com/Rebilly/generator-openapi-repo) tool and [ReDoc](https://github.com/Redocly/redoc) documentation. In addition to standard OpenAPI syntax we use a few [vendor extensions](https://github.com/Redocly/redoc/blob/master/docs/redoc-vendor-extensions.md). # Cross-Origin Resource Sharing This API features Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) implemented in compliance with [W3C spec](https://www.w3.org/TR/cors/). And that allows cross-domain communication from the browser. All responses have a wildcard same-origin which makes them completely public and accessible to everyone, including any code on any site. # Authentication Petstore offers two forms of authentication: - API Key - OAuth2 OAuth2 - an open protocol to allow secure authorization in a simple and standard method from web, mobile and desktop applications. Base URLs: * //petstore.swagger.io/v2 * //petstore.swagger.io/sandbox Terms of service Email: Support Web: Support License: Apache 2.0 # Authentication - oAuth2 authentication. Get access to data while protecting your account credentials. OAuth2 is also a safer and more secure way to give you access. - Flow: implicit - Authorization URL = [http://petstore.swagger.io/api/oauth/dialog](http://petstore.swagger.io/api/oauth/dialog) |Scope|Scope Description| |---|---| |write:pets|modify pets in your account| |read:pets|read your pets| * API Key (api_key) - Parameter Name: **api_key**, in: header. For this sample, you can use the api key `special-key` to test the authorization filters.

pet

Everything about your Pets ## addPet > Code samples ```shell curl --request POST \ --url http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet \ --header 'accept: application/xml' \ --header 'authorization: Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN' \ --header 'content-type: application/json' \ --data '{"id":0,"category":{"id":0,"name":"string","sub":{"prop1":"string"}},"name":"Guru","photoUrls":["string"],"tags":[{"id":0,"name":"string"}],"status":"available","petType":"string"}' ``` ```node const request = require('request'); const options = { method: 'POST', url: 'http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet', headers: { accept: 'application/xml', 'content-type': 'application/json', authorization: 'Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN' }, body: { id: 0, category: {id: 0, name: 'string', sub: {prop1: 'string'}}, name: 'Guru', photoUrls: ['string'], tags: [{id: 0, name: 'string'}], status: 'available', petType: 'string' }, json: true }; request(options, function (error, response, body) { if (error) throw new Error(error); console.log(body); }); ``` ```php setUrl('http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet'); $request->setMethod(HTTP_METH_POST); $request->setHeaders([ 'accept' => 'application/xml', 'content-type' => 'application/json', 'authorization' => 'Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN' ]); $request->setBody('{"id":0,"category":{"id":0,"name":"string","sub":{"prop1":"string"}},"name":"Guru","photoUrls":["string"],"tags":[{"id":0,"name":"string"}],"status":"available","petType":"string"}'); try { $response = $request->send(); echo $response->getBody(); } catch (HttpException $ex) { echo $ex; } ``` ```java HttpResponse response = Unirest.post("http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet") .header("accept", "application/xml") .header("content-type", "application/json") .header("authorization", "Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN") .body("{\"id\":0,\"category\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"sub\":{\"prop1\":\"string\"}},\"name\":\"Guru\",\"photoUrls\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\"}],\"status\":\"available\",\"petType\":\"string\"}") .asString(); ``` ```go package main import ( "fmt" "strings" "net/http" "io/ioutil" ) func main() { url := "http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet" payload := strings.NewReader("{\"id\":0,\"category\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"sub\":{\"prop1\":\"string\"}},\"name\":\"Guru\",\"photoUrls\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\"}],\"status\":\"available\",\"petType\":\"string\"}") req, _ := http.NewRequest("POST", url, payload) req.Header.Add("accept", "application/xml") req.Header.Add("content-type", "application/json") req.Header.Add("authorization", "Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN") res, _ := http.DefaultClient.Do(req) defer res.Body.Close() body, _ := ioutil.ReadAll(res.Body) fmt.Println(res) fmt.Println(string(body)) } ``` ```python import http.client conn = http.client.HTTPConnection("petstore.swagger.io") payload = "{\"id\":0,\"category\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"sub\":{\"prop1\":\"string\"}},\"name\":\"Guru\",\"photoUrls\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\"}],\"status\":\"available\",\"petType\":\"string\"}" headers = { 'accept': "application/xml", 'content-type': "application/json", 'authorization': "Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN" } conn.request("POST", "/v2/pet", payload, headers) res = conn.getresponse() data = res.read() print(data.decode("utf-8")) ``` ```csharp var client = new RestClient("http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet"); var request = new RestRequest(Method.POST); request.AddHeader("accept", "application/xml"); request.AddHeader("content-type", "application/json"); request.AddHeader("authorization", "Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN"); request.AddParameter("application/json", "{\"id\":0,\"category\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"sub\":{\"prop1\":\"string\"}},\"name\":\"Guru\",\"photoUrls\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\"}],\"status\":\"available\",\"petType\":\"string\"}", ParameterType.RequestBody); IRestResponse response = client.Execute(request); ``` ```ruby require 'uri' require 'net/http' url = URI("http://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet") http = Net::HTTP.new(url.host, url.port) request = Net::HTTP::Post.new(url) request["accept"] = 'application/xml' request["content-type"] = 'application/json' request["authorization"] = 'Bearer REPLACE_BEARER_TOKEN' request.body = "{\"id\":0,\"category\":{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\",\"sub\":{\"prop1\":\"string\"}},\"name\":\"Guru\",\"photoUrls\":[\"string\"],\"tags\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"string\"}],\"status\":\"available\",\"petType\":\"string\"}" response = http.request(request) puts response.read_body ``` `POST /pet` *Add a new pet to the store* Add new pet to the store inventory. > Body parameter ```json { "type": "object", "required": [ "name", "photoUrls" ], "discriminator": { "propertyName": "petType" }, "properties": { "id": { "description": "Pet ID", "allOf": [ { "type": "integer", "format": "int64" } ] }, "category": { "description": "Categories this pet belongs to", "allOf": [ { "type": "object", "properties": { "id": { "description": "Category ID", "allOf": [ { "type": "integer", "format": "int64" } ] }, "name": { "description": "Category name", "type": "string", "minLength": 1 }, "sub": { "description": "Test Sub Category", "type": "object", "properties": { "prop1": { "type": "string", "description": "Dumb Property" } } } }, "xml": { "name": "Category" } } ] }, "name": { "description": "The name given to a pet", "type": "string", "example": "Guru" }, "photoUrls": { "description": "The list of URL to a cute photos featuring pet", "type": "array", "xml": { "name": "photoUrl", "wrapped": true }, "items": { "type": "string", "format": "url" } }, "tags": { "description": "Tags attached to the pet", "type": "array", "xml": { "name": "tag", "wrapped": true }, "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "id": { "description": "Tag ID", "allOf": [ { "type": "integer", "format": "int64" } ] },
